    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "James Coyle and A. w. Davis are\nin the city from Republic. They\nsay the town is quiet, but has good\nprospects for general resumption\nin a short time.\n\n\nWork on the new branch railroad\nwhich is surveyed from Curlew to\nMidway, B. c., will be started about\nthe first of February.\n\n\nFrom Midway it will build to the\nlively mining camp of Phoenix\nThis promises to liven things up\nconsiderably in those regions."
    }
